body:
Can we get an update on this issue?
This issue basically prevents the usage of 1.6.0 in any UWP C# project.

I made the smallest possible sample project that reproduces the error.

Just try to build it using Debug | x64:
[issue6249sample.zip](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/5860598/issue6249sample.zip)
I'm currently having the same issue and it is currently preventing me in using any model made with the Model Builder, since it outputs as a 1.6 .onnx.

Hi,

Thanks for reporting this.

We are aware of the issue in the NuGet package layout that is causing multiple versions of the same dll to be simultaneously bin placed.

We are actively working on this issue!
I installed version 1.7.0 via nuget and I get the same error.

> I installed version 1.7.0 via nuget and I get the same error.

Yes, it seems that the error has not been fixed.
```
1>  C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\2019\Enterprise\MSBuild\Microsoft\VisualStudio\v16.0\AppxPackage\Microsoft.AppXPackage.Targets(6140,5): error APPX1111: Payload contains two or more files with the same destination path 'Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning.dll', but they are different sizes. Source files: 
1>C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\2019\Enterprise\MSBuild\Microsoft\VisualStudio\v16.0\AppxPackage\Microsoft.AppXPackage.Targets(6140,5): error APPX1111: C:\Users\hig\.nuget\packages\microsoft.ai.machinelearning\1.7.0\build\uap\..\..\runtimes\win-x64\uap\Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning.dll
1>C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\2019\Enterprise\MSBuild\Microsoft\VisualStudio\v16.0\AppxPackage\Microsoft.AppXPackage.Targets(6140,5): error APPX1111: C:\Users\hig\.nuget\packages\microsoft.ai.machinelearning\1.7.0\runtimes\win-x64\native\static\microsoft.ai.machinelearning.dll
```

Unfortunately, this fix did not make it into the 1.7.0 release.

It has been fixed in master. The fix should become available in the next release.

I see. Thank you for taking the trouble.
I will wait for the next release.
I checked the new 1.8.0 release and this problem is now fixed. Thanks.
This issue is back in version 1.10.0. Version 1.9.1 is fine.

Hi, thank you for reporting this issue.

I created blank UWP applications in C++ and C# in VS2019 and VS2022 and was not able to reproduce the issue.
Have you tried a clean build?

Thanks,

I see it now. Happens on build. I'll take a look.

This has been resolved in master with this change: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/10076
A build from source version of the NuGet package can be built by using the following build.bat parameters:

--enable_wcos
--ms_experimental
--use_dml
--use_winml
--build
--build_nuget
i have this problem with 1.11.0 and 1.10.0 Nuget
Confirming this in 1.12.1
How do i resolve this issue?

With the `Blank App, Packaged (WinUI 3 in Desktop)` Template no version of the nuget package will work.

I've tried versions `1.15.1`,  `1.10`, `1.9.1`,  `1.8.1`.

```
1>\source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.WindowsAppSDK.1.2.221109.1\build\Microsoft.Build.Msix.Packaging.targets(1504,5): error APPX1101: Payload contains two or more files with the same destination path 'microsoft.ai.machinelearning.dll'. Source files: 
1>\source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.WindowsAppSDK.1.2.221109.1\build\Microsoft.Build.Msix.Packaging.targets(1504,5): error APPX1101: C:\Users\a\source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning.1.15.1\runtimes\win-x64\_native\microsoft.ai.machinelearning.dll
1>\source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.WindowsAppSDK.1.2.221109.1\build\Microsoft.Build.Msix.Packaging.targets(1504,5): error APPX1101: \source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning.1.15.1\winmds\microsoft.ai.machinelearning.dll
```

The folder `\source\repos\App5\packages\Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning.1.15.1\winmds` only has a `microsoft.ai.machinelearning.winmd` file not a dll.

@smk2007 would it be possible to get something working for WinUI3. I've waiting on this sometime https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/14915

Maybe I could manually copy across the dll, and add the header directory.

@juwens, @SuavePirate , @Walia8416,  @tom-huntington - 
From what I can gather, there is an issue with adding the Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning NuGet Package across various versions (1.10, 1.11, 1.12).

However, I am unable to repro this problem in VS2022 with the latest Microsoft.AI.MachineLearning NuGet package (1.15.1).
I have tried the following project templates:
  - C# Blank App (Universal Windows)
  - C# Blank App, Packaged (WinUI 3 in Desktop)
  - C# Console App with <TargetFramework>net7.0-windows10.0.19041.0</TargetFramework>
  - Blank App (C++/WinRT) UWP
  - Windows Console Application (C++/WinRT)
  - C++ Console App
  
  Can you please share your configuration that is currently causing problems?
  
@tom-huntington,
Regarding the C# Blank App, Packaged (WinUI 3 in Desktop), I have created the following PR ( https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/16415) to address the issue.
If you would like to verify that this works with your applications feel free to checkout the branch in the PR and run a local build.

These parameters will be needed to produce a local package to verify.
--enable_wcos
--ms_experimental
--use_dml
--use_winml
--build
--build_nuget

> @tom-huntington, Regarding the C# Blank App, Packaged (WinUI 3 in Desktop), I have created the following PR ( #16415) to address the issue.

I patched the `.tagrets` file locally, and now it builds. Thanks!
Closing as fixed.
